#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.54:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.54:0.2"
msgid "6. Nīvaraṇavagga"
msgstr "6. Hindrances"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: asamaya-samayasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.54:0.3"
msgid "54. Samayasutta"
msgstr "54. Times Good for Meditation"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.66"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, asamayā padhānāya."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are five times that are not good for meditation."

msgctxt "an5.54:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.54:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jiṇṇo hoti jarāyābhibhūto."
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant is old, overcome with old age."

msgctxt "an5.54:1.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo asamayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the first time that’s not good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu byādhito hoti byādhinābhibhūto."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant is sick, overcome by sickness."

msgctxt "an5.54:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo asamayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the second time that’s not good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, dubbhikkhaṃ hoti dussassaṃ dullabhapiṇḍaṃ, na "
"sukaraṃ uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s a famine, a bad harvest, so it’s hard to get alms-food, "
"and not easy to keep going by collecting alms."

msgctxt "an5.54:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo asamayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the third time that’s not good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhayaṃ hoti aṭavisaṅkopo, cakkasamārūḷhā jānapadā "
"pariyāyanti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s peril from wild savages, and the countryfolk mount "
"their vehicles and flee everywhere."

msgctxt "an5.54:4.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho asamayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the fourth time that’s not good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, saṅgho bhinno hoti."
msgstr "Furthermore, there’s a schism in the Saṅgha."

# BB follows the comm in translating parikkhepa (see his note). But in the Vinaya it always has a meaning of “enclosure”, typically a fence that surrounds a monastery or village. It makes perfect sense here, either literally, with a sanghakamma that restricts movement as contrasted with pariccaja as expulsion, or else as “shutting down” in argument.
msgctxt "an5.54:5.2"
msgid ""
"Saṅghe kho pana, bhikkhave, bhinne aññamaññaṃ akkosā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ "
"paribhāsā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ parikkhepā ca honti, aññamaññaṃ pariccajā ca "
"honti."
msgstr ""
"When the Saṅgha is split, they abuse, insult, block, and reject each other."

msgctxt "an5.54:5.3"
msgid ""
"Tattha appasannā ceva nappasīdanti, pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"This doesn’t inspire confidence in those without it, and it causes some with "
"confidence to change their minds."

msgctxt "an5.54:5.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo asamayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the fifth time that’s not good for meditation."

msgctxt "an5.54:5.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca asamayā padhānāyāti."
msgstr "These are the five times that are not good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:6.1"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, samayā padhānāya."
msgstr "There are five times that are good for meditation."

msgctxt "an5.54:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.54:6.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu daharo hoti yuvā susu kāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena "
"samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā."
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant is a youth, young, black-haired, blessed with youth, in "
"the prime of life."

msgctxt "an5.54:6.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo samayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the first time that’s good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:7.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appābādho hoti appātaṅko, samavepākiniyā "
"gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, they are rarely ill or unwell. Their stomach digests well, "
"being neither too hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation."

msgctxt "an5.54:7.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo samayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the second time that’s good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.67"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:8.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, subhikkhaṃ hoti susassaṃ sulabhapiṇḍaṃ, sukaraṃ "
"uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, there’s plenty of food, a good harvest, so it’s easy to get "
"alms-food, and easy to keep going by collecting alms."

msgctxt "an5.54:8.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo samayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the third time that’s good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:9.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, manussā samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā "
"khīrodakībhūtā aññamaññaṃ piyacakkhūhi sampassantā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, people live in harmony, appreciating each other, without "
"quarreling, blending like milk and water, and regarding each other with "
"kindly eyes."

msgctxt "an5.54:9.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho samayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the fourth time that’s good for meditation."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an5.54:10.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, saṃgho samaggo sammodamāno avivadamāno ekuddeso "
"phāsu viharati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, the Saṅgha lives comfortably, in harmony, appreciating each "
"other, without quarreling, with one recitation."

msgctxt "an5.54:10.2"
msgid ""
"Saṃghe kho pana, bhikkhave, samagge na ceva aññamaññaṃ akkosā honti, na ca "
"aññamaññaṃ paribhāsā honti, na ca aññamaññaṃ parikkhepā honti, na ca "
"aññamaññaṃ pariccajā honti."
msgstr ""
"When the Saṅgha is in harmony, they don’t abuse, insult, block, or reject "
"each other."

#. VAR: bhiyyobhāvo → bhīyobhāvo (pts1) | bhiyyobhāvāya (mr)
msgctxt "an5.54:10.3"
msgid "Tattha appasannā ceva pasīdanti, pasannānañca bhiyyobhāvo hoti."
msgstr ""
"This inspires confidence in those without it, and increases confidence in "
"those who have it."

msgctxt "an5.54:10.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo samayo padhānāya."
msgstr "This is the fifth time that’s good for meditation."

msgctxt "an5.54:10.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca samayā padhānāyā”ti."
msgstr "These are the five times that are good for meditation.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.54:10.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
